<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
     <questestinterop>
       <item ident="tca23">
         <presentation>
           <material>
             <mattext texttype="text/plain">You are looking at the first step in the TCA
cycle where citrate is formed from oxaloacetate
and acetyl-coA by the enzyme citrate synthase.

The following two steps (2 &amp; 3) ultimately lead to oxidation of the -OH group in citrate, along with release of a CO2.   
             
&lt;b&gt;Which of the following occurs in the &lt;u&gt;first&lt;/u&gt; of these two steps?&lt;/b&gt;

[You cannot advance to the next step until you select the correct answer.]
             </mattext></material>
           <response_lid rcardinality="Single" ident="tca23">
             <render_choice>
               <response_label ident="Res1">
                 <material>
                   <mattext texttype="text/plain">Oxidation of the -OH to C=O.</mattext></material></response_label>
               <response_label ident="Res2">
                 <material>
                   <mattext texttype="text/plain">Loss of CO2.</mattext></material></response_label>
               <response_label ident="Res3">
               <material>
                 <mattext texttype="text/plain">Movement of the -OH group.</mattext></material></response_label>
               </render_choice>
           </response_lid>
         </presentation>
         <resprocessing>
           <outcomes>
             <decvar varname="SCORE" vartype="integer"/></outcomes>
           <respcondition>
             <conditionvar>
               <varequal respident="tca23_01">Res1</varequal>
             </conditionvar>
             <setvar varname="SCORE">0</setvar>
             <displayfeedback feedbacktype="Response" linkrefid="FeedBack0"/>
           </respcondition>
           <respcondition>
             <conditionvar>
               <varequal respident="tca23_02">Res2</varequal></conditionvar>
             <setvar varname="SCORE">0</setvar>
             <displayfeedback feedbacktype="Response" linkrefid="FeedBack1"/></respcondition>
           <respcondition>
             <conditionvar>
               <varequal respident="tca23_03">Res3</varequal></conditionvar>
             <setvar varname="SCORE">10</setvar>
             <displayfeedback feedbacktype="Response" linkrefid="FeedBack2"/></respcondition>
         </resprocessing>
       
         <itemfeedback ident="hint">
           <hint>
             <hintmaterial>
               <material>
                 <mattext texttype="text/plain">Remember that carbon can only form four bonds.</mattext></material>
             </hintmaterial>          
               <hintmaterial>
                 <material>
                   <mattext texttype="text/plain">The oxidation of an -OH produces a ketone C=O, leaving only two additional bonds.</mattext></material>
               </hintmaterial>          
             </hint>
         </itemfeedback>
         <itemfeedback ident="FeedBack0">
           <material>
             <mattext texttype="text/plain">Incorrect, how many bonds would the carbon have then?</mattext></material></itemfeedback>
         <itemfeedback ident="FeedBack1">
           <material>
             <mattext texttype="text/plain">Incorrect, this does not happen until you can perform the oxidation.</mattext></material></itemfeedback>
         <itemfeedback ident="FeedBack2">
           <material>
             <mattext texttype="text/plain">Correct, this allows the oxidation of a secondary carbon.
After moving the -OH group, it can now be oxidized along with release of CO2, to give alpha-ketoglutarate.
             </mattext></material></itemfeedback>
        </item>
     </questestinterop>
